cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CR 

This paper is about automatic misinformation identification on social media, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also deals with social media data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The attention mechanism used in the proposed approach is a machine learning technique, which could place the paper in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves data mining and machine learning techniques, which could also place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
